Who We Are:

At ASC Consultants, we are a team of experts, consultants and specialists in food and beverage manufacturing who specialize in Food Safety and Quality, system development, implementation, certification and mitigating risk programs. We leverage the knowledge of our team’s expertise to support the growth and success of our clients by focusing on the foundation of a culture of quality and food safety. Our goals are achieved through collaboration, compliance protocol, and a shared passion and vision for a world where we can trust and enjoy the foods and beverages we consume and work with our clients from all over the world to assure safe and product of the highest quality from farms to finished goods.

Title: Technical Assistant

Reports to: Operations Manager

Location: Remote

Compensation: Starting at $30/hour (based on experience)

Role Overview:

We are looking for a highly organized and technically adept individual to support the digital, data, and documentation systems that enable ASC’s consulting teams to deliver high-quality work. This role centers on managing and manipulating structured data, maintaining quality documentation systems, and developing tools for inventory management and cost-of-goods analysis.

A strong working knowledge of AI tools and practical AI application is essential. The ideal candidate is comfortable evaluating data workflows, using AI systems to enhance efficiency, and integrating AI-driven processes into documentation management, tool development, and client-facing deliverables.

This role is well-suited for someone who approaches technical problems with a scientific mindset, values accuracy, and enjoys building clean, functional solutions that strengthen operational and quality programs.

Main Responsibilities:

Data & Digital Tool Development

Build and maintain spreadsheet-based and lightweight database tools supporting Quality, Compliance, Inventory, and COGS workflows.
Manipulate, clean, and organize datasets to support client projects and internal systems.
Use advanced spreadsheet logic and basic scripting to streamline data processing.
Produce structured reports, trend analyses, visual dashboards, and summaries.
Validate data accuracy and ensure reliable outputs for consultants and clients.
AI-Driven Workflow Support

AI knowledge, interest and experience to build additional ai infrastructure within company
Apply AI tools to automate routine data tasks, documentation cleanup, version standardization, and report generation.
Support development of AI-assisted systems for data validation, document structuring, and inventory/COGS logic.
Evaluate emerging AI tools and determine where they can be safely and effectively integrated into ASC systems and client workflows.
Maintain structured prompt libraries and ensure proper documentation of AI-assisted processes.
Quality Documentation & System Organization

Maintain and standardize digital document systems supporting quality, food safety, regulatory, and operational programs.
Create and format templates, logs, checklists, and controlled documents.
Organize files, maintain naming conventions, and support controlled document workflows across departments.
Inventory & Cost-of-Goods Support

Cost Accounting & Inventory system understanding
Develop structured tools to support raw material tracking, inventory logic, production costing, and finished goods cost models.
Support transitions from legacy spreadsheets to more scalable or cloud-based models.
Build cost-effective solutions suitable for SMB-level operations and resource constraints.
Operational & Project Support

Assist consultants in preparing meeting materials, tracking project tasks, and managing client deliverables.
Create spreadsheets, documents, and slide decks for internal use and client communication.
Collect and structure data supporting quality metrics, operational KPIs, and system audits.
Required Skills & Qualifications

Strong computer skills with advanced proficiency in Excel, Google Sheets, and general data handling.
Demonstrated ability to structure, clean, and analyze complex datasets.
Strong working knowledge of AI tools
Ability to use AI safely for drafting, structuring, or automating tasks without compromising regulatory integrity or client confidentiality
Strong organizational skills and experience managing digital documentation systems.
Experience with:
Excel/Google Sheets (advanced formulas preferred)
SmartSheets
Wherefour
Database development or platform transfers
Experience with technical tools used in product-based businesses (inventory, compliance, costing)
